Synopsis

Anupama (Mamtha Mohandas) is the only child of the business magnate GK (Gopala Krishnan - Cohin Haneefa), who owns the hugely successful Parvana Group of companies in the middle east. While she is in India to be the special guest of a reality show and to promote a few charity drives by Parvana Group, she meets Humayoon (Rehman) who introduces himself as a musician from a very ordinary background. Humayoon requests Anu to sponsor his dream project - a symphony that would be the fusion of Eastern & Western music.
